This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with kernel-based learning and proposes a novel training strategy for optimizing kernel mappings. It may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as kernel methods are commonly used in image processing and computer vision tasks. Additionally, the paper mentions experimental results on datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses stochastic gradient methods, which may also place it in the category of cs.SD (Software Engineering).
